'''Billy Eichner''' (born September 18, 1978) is an American comedian, actor, writer, and television personality, commonly focusing on self-deprecation and pop culture. He is the star, executive producer and creator of [[Funny Or Die]]'s ''[[Billy on the Street]]'', a comedy game show that airs on [[truTV]]. Eichner was nominated for a Daytime Emmy Award for "Outstanding Game Show Host" in 2013. He is also known for playing [[Craig Middlebrooks]] on the sitcom ''[[Parks and Recreation]]''.
Eichner starred in the [[Hulu]] original series ''[[Difficult People]]'' alongside [[Julie Klausner]] and he had a recurring role in the [[American Horror Story: Cult|seventh season]] of ''[[American Horror Story]]'', which premiered on September 5, 2017, where he portrayed Harrison Wilton. In April 2018 Eichner was confirmed to appear in the eighth season of the show.
==Personal life== Eichner is [[Jewish]],<ref>{{cite news|last=Kensky|first=Eitan|title=Billy Eichner Is the Funniest Man on the Internet|date=March 14, 2013|url=http://blogs.forward.com/the-arty-semite/172841/billy-eichner-is-the-funniest-man-on-the-internet|accessdate=November 16, 2013|newspaper=[[The Jewish Daily Forward]]}}</ref> and is also openly gay.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2015/10/billy-eichner-is-only-shouting-because-new-york-is-loud|title=Billy Eichner is Only Shouting Because New York Is Loud|work=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]|accessdate=October 5, 2015|date=November 2015|first=David|last=Kamp}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2013/02/12/how-billy-on-the-street-host-billy-eichner-hit-the-mainstream.html|title=How ‘Billy on the Street’ Host Billy Eichner Hit the Mainstream|work=[[The Daily Beast]]|accessdate=August 21, 2014|date=February 12, 2013|first=Kevin|last=Fallon}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.backstage.com/review/ny-theater/off-broadway/billy-eichner-gay-white-and-terrified|title=Billy Eichner: Gay, White, and Terrified!|publisher=[[Backstage (magazine)|Backstage]]|accessdate=August 21, 2014|first=Mark| last=Peikert|date=May 27, 2009}}</ref> He graduated from [[Stuyvesant High School]] in 1996<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm2813994/|title=Billy Eichner|accessdate=February 18, 2014}}</ref> two years ahead of fellow actors [[Telly Leung]] and [[Malcolm Barrett (actor)|Malcolm Barrett]] and from [[Northwestern University]] in 2000.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/billy-eichner/bio/355096/|title=Billy Eichner Biography|accessdate=July 22, 2015}}</ref> Actor [[Robin Lord Taylor]] was his college roommate.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Wagner|first1=Curt|title=Robin Lord Taylor walks the walk as Penguin in 'Gotham'|url=http://www.redeyechicago.com/entertainment/tv/redeye-robin-lord-taylor-interview-gotham-penguin-20141005-story.html|accessdate=January 12, 2017|work=[[RedEye]]|date=October 5, 2014}}</ref>
==Career== Eichner gained attention as the host and writer of ''Creation Nation: A Live Talk Show'', a critically acclaimed stage show in New York.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2005/05/15/theater/newsandfeatures/15calh.html|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|title=Hey Gang, Let's Put On a Twisted Talk Show|accessdate=August 21, 2014|date=May 15, 2005|first=Ada|last=Calhoun}}</ref> He also appeared on ''[[Conan (talk show)|Conan]]'' as a special correspondent in original video shorts<ref>{{cite web|url=http://teamcoco.com/content/team-coco-heads-superbowl|title=Team Coco Heads To The Superbowl! [sic]|accessdate=August 21, 2014|date=February 3, 2012|publisher=teamcoco.com}}</ref> and as himself on [[Bravo (U.S. TV channel)|Bravo]]'s ''[[Watch What Happens: Live]]'' with [[Andy Cohen (television personality)|Andy Cohen]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bravotv.com/watch-what-happens-live/season-6/photos/show-shots/martha-plimpton-and-billy-eichner|title= Watch What Happens Live - Martha Plimpton and Billy Eichner|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131015050023/http://www.bravotv.com/watch-what-happens-live/season-6/photos/show-shots/martha-plimpton-and-billy-eichner|archivedate=October 15, 2013 |accessdate=August 1, 2012|publisher=[[Bravo (U.S. TV channel)|BravoTV]]}}</ref> ''[[Last Call with Carson Daly]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nbc.com/last-call-with-carson-daly/episode-guide/12192011.shtml|title=Last Call with Carson Daly |publisher= [[NBC]]|accessdate=August 21, 2014}}</ref> ''[[The Wendy Williams Show]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wendyshow.com/2012/02/24/latoya-jackson-90210-the-cw |title=LaToya Jackson and Billy Eichner |accessdate=August 21, 2014 |publisher=[[The Wendy Williams Show]] |date=February 24, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141228103445/http://www.wendyshow.com/2012/02/24/latoya-jackson-90210-the-cw/ |archivedate=December 28, 2014 |df= }}</ref> and ''[[Fashion Police]]'' with [[Joan Rivers]], among others.
Eichner has been a [[voiceover]] guest star in several episodes of the [[Cartoon series|animated TV series]] ''[[Bob's Burgers]]'' as Mr. Ambrose, the Librarian. He has been a regular performer at New York City's [[Upright Citizens Brigade Theatre]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ucbcomedy.com/talent/view/1826/billy-eichner|title=Billy Eichner|accessdate=August 1, 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101022060111/http://www.ucbcomedy.com/talent/view/1826/billy-eichner|archivedate=October 22, 2010|publisher=ucbcomedy.com}}</ref>
On August 5, 2013, Eichner guest starred in the [[Parks and Recreation (season 6)|sixth season]] of ''[[Parks and Recreation]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://splitsider.com/2013/08/billy-eichner-to-play-donna|title=Billy Eichner to Play Donna's Doppelganger on 'Parks and Rec'|publisher=[[Splitsider]]|accessdate=August 21, 2014|first=Bradford|last=Evans|date=August 5, 2013}}</ref> Eichner's first episode aired on October 10, 2013. He stars as [[Donna Meagle|Donna's]] Eagleton counterpart, Craig Middlebrooks, who joins the [[Pawnee (Parks and Recreation)|Pawnee]] Parks and Recreation Department when Pawnee absorbs Eagleton.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/10/10/billy-eichner-parks-and-rec_n_4073919.html?ir=Comedy|title= Billy Eichner On 'Parks And Recreation' – And Every Other Show Ever, Please (PHOTOS)|accessdate=August 21, 2014|newspaper=[[The Huffington Post]]|date=October 10, 2013|first=Maggie|last=Furlong}}</ref> He became a series regular in episode four of the seventh season of the show.
During the [[66th Primetime Emmy Awards]] show in 2014, Eichner appeared with show host [[Seth Meyers]] on the streets of New York, interviewing random people.<ref>{{cite web|first=Eric|last=Shorey|title=Billy Eichner and Seth Meyers Harass New Yorkers About The Emmy Awards|url=http://www.thebacklot.com/billy-eichner-and-seth-meyers-harass-new-yorkers-about-the-emmy-awards/08/2014|publisher=thebacklot.com|accessdate=December 27, 2014}}</ref>
Eichner starred in a ''[[Hulu]]'' original series titled ''[[Difficult People]]'' with Julie Klausner, and executive produced by [[Amy Poehler]], The project was originally set up at [[USA Network]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.hulu.com/2014/11/18/hulu-orders-amy-poehlers-difficult-people-starring-julie-klausner-and-billy-eichner/|title=Hulu Orders Amy Poehler’s Difficult People Starring Julie Klausner and Billy Eichner|work=[[Hulu]]}}</ref> The series began airing on August 5, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vulture.com/2015/06/watch-the-first-difficult-people-teaser.html|title=Watch the First Difficult People Teaser -- Vulture|work=Vulture}}</ref> In 2016, Eichner appeared in ''[[Neighbors 2: Sorority Rising]]'', released on May 20.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kroll|first1=Justin|title=Billy Eichner Joins Cast of ‘Neighbors 2’|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/billy-eichner-neighbors-2-1201601900/|accessdate=October 30, 2015}}</ref> In March 2017, it was announced that Eichner would be joining the cast of ''[[American Horror Story]]'' for a recurring role in its seventh season.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Stack|first1=Tim|title='American Horror Story': Billy Eichner Cast in Season 7|url=http://ew.com/tv/2017/03/28/american-horror-story-billy-eichner-season-7/|website=EW.com|accessdate=March 30, 2017|date=March 28, 2017}}</ref> In April 2017, it was reported that Eichner was in talks with Disney and director [[Jon Favreau]] to provide the voice of [[Timon and Pumbaa|Timon]] in Disney's live action remake of ''[[The Lion King]]''.,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/lion-king-cast-seth-rogen-billy-eichner-talks-voice-timon-pumba-997310|title=Seth Rogen, Billy Eichner in Talks to Voice Timon and Pumbaa in New 'Lion King'|last=Galuppo|first=Mia|date=April 25, 2017|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=26 April 2017}}</ref> which was confirmed in November 2017 by [[Disney]]'s official Twitter account.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=Disney|author-link=Disney|number=925853092255551488|date= November 1, 2017|title=#TheLionKing. 2019. 🦁👑|accessdate=November 3, 2017 }}</ref>
==Political==
On February 1, 2018, Eichner announced a new initiative called Glam Up the Midterms, during that night’s episode of [[Jimmy Kimmel Live]] in conjunction with Funny or Die and with the support of several late night hosts including [[Sarah Silverman]], [[James Corden]], [[Seth Meyers]], [[Jimmy Kimmel]], [[Conan O’Brien]], [[John Oliver]], [[Chelsea Handler]], [[Robin Thede]], and [[Andy Cohen (television personality)|Andy Cohen]]. Glam Up the Midterm’s purpose is getting people to vote in the November 6, 2018 midterm elections, especially millennials of whom only 12% voted in the previous midterm election.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/glam-up-the-midterms-2018-billy-eichner-john-oliver-andy-cohen-millennial-voting-campaign|title=Billy Eichner, John Oliver, Andy Cohen, and More Are Joining Forces to Glam Up the Midterms|work=Vogue|access-date=2018-03-01|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mashable.com/2018/02/02/billy-eichner-launches-glam-up-the-mid-terms/#VUSn_lIrM5qS|title=Billy Eichner is on a mission to make the mid-terms glam again|last=Hamilton|first=Isobel|work=Mashable|access-date=2018-03-01|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/billy-eichner-launches-star-studded-campaign-get-millennials-vote-midterm-elections-1081342|title=Billy Eichner Launches Star-Studded Campaign to Get Millennials to Vote in Midterm Elections|work=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=2018-03-01|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://glamupthemidterms.com/|title=Glam Up The Midterms|website=glamupthemidterms.com|language=en|access-date=2018-03-01}}</ref>
